<section class="brand--ministry-of-defence brand__border-color organisation__brand-border-top organisation__section-wrap organisation__margin-bottom" id="featured-documents">
  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--padding gem-c-heading--margin-bottom-2  ">Featured</h2>

    </div>
  </div>


    <div class="grid-row">
        <div class="column-one-third">
            <div class="gem-c-image-card  brand--ministry-of-defence">
    <figure class="gem-c-image-card__image-wrapper"><img class="gem-c-image-card__image" alt="left to right: Dstl Chief Executive Gary Aitkenhead and DECA Chief Executive Geraint Spearing" src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/feature/image/69132/s465_Dstl_partnering_agreement.jpg"></img></figure>

    <div class="gem-c-image-card__text-wrapper">
      <p class="gem-c-image-card__context"><time datetime="2019-02-25">25 February 2019</time><span aria-hidden="true"> — </span>Press release</p>

        <h3 class="gem-c-image-card__title">
              <a class="gem-c-image-card__title-link brand__color" href="/government/news/mod-sealand-to-be-innovation-hotbed-for-defence">MOD Sealand to be innovation hotbed for Defence</a>
</h3>
      <div class="gem-c-image-card__description"><div class="govspeak">
<p>The Defence Science and Technology Laboratory (Dstl), which develops cutting-edge science and technology to keep the UK safe from harm, has opened an office within the Defence Electronics and Components Agency (DECA) in MOD Sealand in North Wales.</p>
</div></div>


    </div>
  </div>

        </div>
        <div class="column-one-third">
            <div class="gem-c-image-card  brand--ministry-of-defence">
    <figure class="gem-c-image-card__image-wrapper"><img class="gem-c-image-card__image" alt="UK F-35B" src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/feature/image/68868/s465_F-35_tier_2.jpg"></img></figure>

    <div class="gem-c-image-card__text-wrapper">
      <p class="gem-c-image-card__context"><time datetime="2019-02-12">12 February 2019</time><span aria-hidden="true"> — </span>News story</p>

        <h3 class="gem-c-image-card__title">
              <a class="gem-c-image-card__title-link brand__color" href="/government/news/uk-wins-global-f-35-support-assignment-worth-500m">UK wins global F-35 support assignment worth £500M</a>
</h3>
      <div class="gem-c-image-card__description"><div class="govspeak">
<p>The UK’s role as a leading partner on the global F-35 programme has received another huge boost today.</p>
</div></div>


    </div>
  </div>

        </div>
        <div class="column-one-third">
            <div class="gem-c-image-card  brand--ministry-of-defence">
    <figure class="gem-c-image-card__image-wrapper"><img class="gem-c-image-card__image" alt="Special Projects Communications and Force Protection Delivery Team meet with DECA Chief Executive Geraint Spearing, Business Development Director, Ian Cole and members of the Managed Services Team" src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/feature/image/65990/s465_Force_protection_Sept_19_18.jpg"></img></figure>

    <div class="gem-c-image-card__text-wrapper">
      <p class="gem-c-image-card__context"><time datetime="2018-09-28">28 September 2018</time><span aria-hidden="true"> — </span>News story</p>

        <h3 class="gem-c-image-card__title">
              <a class="gem-c-image-card__title-link brand__color" href="/government/news/deca-wins-48-m-support-work-contract">DECA WINS £4.8 M SUPPORT WORK CONTRACT</a>
</h3>
      <div class="gem-c-image-card__description"><div class="govspeak">
<p>The Special Projects Communications and Force Protection Delivery Team (SPCFP DT) is pleased to announce it has placed a £4.8M task with the Defence Electronic Components Agency (DECA) based in North Wales for the support of life saving equipment used by the Armed Services.</p>
</div></div>


    </div>
  </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-row">
        <div class="column-one-third">
            <div class="gem-c-image-card  brand--ministry-of-defence">
    <figure class="gem-c-image-card__image-wrapper"><img class="gem-c-image-card__image" alt="Jason Leeks, DECA Head of Strategy and Governance hosted the Deeside Enterprise Zone (DEZ) Board and Welsh Government’s Economy Secretary, Mr Ken Skates who was in attendance at this particularly important meeting of the Enterprise Zone Board." src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/feature/image/64475/s465_AMRI.jpg"></img></figure>

    <div class="gem-c-image-card__text-wrapper">
      <p class="gem-c-image-card__context"><time datetime="2018-07-20">20 July 2018</time><span aria-hidden="true"> — </span>Press release</p>

        <h3 class="gem-c-image-card__title">
              <a class="gem-c-image-card__title-link brand__color" href="/government/news/welsh-government-working-with-deca-on-plans-for-second-welsh-advanced-manufacturing-and-research-institute">Welsh Government working with DECA on plans for second Welsh Advanced Manufacturing and Research Institute</a>
</h3>
      <div class="gem-c-image-card__description"><div class="govspeak">
<p>The Welsh Government has made significant progress in its plans to establish a second Advanced Manufacturing and Research Institute (AMRI) in North Wales, Economy Secretary Ken Skates has said,</p>
</div></div>


    </div>
  </div>

        </div>
        <div class="column-one-third">
            <div class="gem-c-image-card  brand--ministry-of-defence">
    <figure class="gem-c-image-card__image-wrapper"><img class="gem-c-image-card__image" alt="Secretary of State for Defence Rt Hon Sir Michael Fallon getting hands on experience of DECA’s surface mount repair capability in the dedicated DECA Capability Development training area with Rich Smith.  Copyright DECA" src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/feature/image/57131/s465_Web_1.jpg"></img></figure>

    <div class="gem-c-image-card__text-wrapper">
      <p class="gem-c-image-card__context"><time datetime="2017-10-05"> 5 October 2017</time><span aria-hidden="true"> — </span>News story</p>

        <h3 class="gem-c-image-card__title">
              <a class="gem-c-image-card__title-link brand__color" href="/government/news/secretary-of-state-for-defence-visits-deca-sealand">Secretary of State for Defence visits DECA Sealand</a>
</h3>
      <div class="gem-c-image-card__description"><div class="govspeak">
<p>The Right Honourable Sir Michael Fallon MP visited the Defence Electronics and Components Agency (DECA) Sealand site to experience close up the critical support that DECA provides to the UK’s Armed Forces.</p>
</div></div>


    </div>
  </div>

        </div>
        <div class="column-one-third">
            <div class="gem-c-image-card  brand--ministry-of-defence">
    <figure class="gem-c-image-card__image-wrapper"><img class="gem-c-image-card__image" alt="Dickie Davies, Deputy Director Welsh Government presents to the Aerospace Wales members forum © DECA" src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/feature/image/54232/s465_Aerospace_Wales.jpg"></img></figure>

    <div class="gem-c-image-card__text-wrapper">
      <p class="gem-c-image-card__context"><time datetime="2017-06-16">16 June 2017</time><span aria-hidden="true"> — </span>News story</p>

        <h3 class="gem-c-image-card__title">
              <a class="gem-c-image-card__title-link brand__color" href="/government/news/aerospace-wales-forum-hosted-by-deca">Aerospace Wales Forum hosted by DECA</a>
</h3>
      <div class="gem-c-image-card__description"><div class="govspeak">
<p>The Defence Electronics and Components Agency (DECA) was delighted to host members of the Aerospace Wales Forum welcoming over 40 guests from industry, government and academia to the Sealand site.</p>
</div></div>


    </div>
